f await_daemon_cleanup && std::time::Instant::now() < grace_deadline {\n            tokio::time::sleep(std::time::Duration::from_millis(100)).await;\n            continue;\n        }\n\n        let release_result = LeaseService::release(store, worktree, base_dir, base_dir, &lease);\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_49","type":"agent_message","text":"# Feature: Final Review Safety Hardening\n\n## Description\nLoops 001-016 already cover the v1 rewrite roadmap: workspace/init/config, fixed flow discovery, canonical project/run storage and journal queries, structured stage contracts and renderers, agent execution, standard/docs/ci/quick_dev execution, retry/resume/failure classes, completion/amendments, rollback, requirements drafting, daemon routing/tasks/leases/watchers, and conformance/CI. Loop 17 advanced through `completing -> final_review -> planning`, but the checkpoint history shows no post-review implementation commit, and the current code still contains accepted release-blocking gaps: CLI `run start`/`run resume` bypass the per-project writer lock, daemon dispatch mutates process-global CWD, claim-time journal failures can strand a task in `Claimed` with a live lease and abort the daemon, lease cleanup reports can claim success when cleanup failed, and transient `.claude`/`.ralph/tmp` artifacts remain tracked. This feature closes those remaining safety and release-hygiene gaps without introducing new product surface.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `ralph-burning run start` and `ralph-burning run resume` acquire the same per-project writer lock used by daemon task dispatch before any run-state mutation, and they release it on success, handled error, and early return.\n- [ ] If the CLI cannot obtain the writer lock because another CLI or daemon worker already holds it, the command exits non-zero with an explicit lock-held message and does not create or resume a competing active run.\n- [ ] Daemon worktree dispatch no longer calls `std::env::set_current_dir`; any execution path that needs a working directory receives it explicitly, so daemon behavior is independent of process-global CWD.\n- [ ] `claim_task` becomes rollback-atomic across task state, lease state, and daemon journal writes: if any post-claim journal append fails, the durable end state must never be `Claimed` with a retained lease and writer lock.\n- [ ] Claim failure invariants are explicit: if `LeaseAcquired` journaling fails before `TaskClaimed`, the task ends either `Pending` with no lease/worktree/writer lock or `Failed` with explicit failure class such as `claim_journal_failed`, and the journal contains enough compensating evidence to explain the cleanup outcome.\n- [ ] A single task claim/journal failure is treated as a per-task failure only; `daemon start` continues scanning and may still process other eligible tasks in the same cycle.\n- [ ] `LeaseService::reconcile` and daemon shutdown cleanup surface per-lease cleanup failures explicitly. `released_lease_ids` and user-visible release counts include only leases whose worktree removal, lease-file deletion, task lease-reference clearing, and writer-lock release all succeeded.\n- [ ] Reconcile failure invariants are explicit: if task failure marking succeeds but lease cleanup fails, the task remains terminal but still recoverable for a later reconcile; if lease removal succeeds but task reference clearing fails, the lease is not reported as released and the task remains visibly inconsistent for operator repair.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning daemon reconcile` prints a cleanup failure summary and exits non-zero when any stale lease cannot be fully cleaned up.\n- [ ] Repository hygiene is enforced: `.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock`, `.ralph/tmp/`, and generated runtime-log files are ignored or removed from tracking, and the repository no longer carries committed transient session/runtime artifacts.\n- [ ] Regression coverage is added for CLI writer-lock contention, panic/error-safe lock release, no process-global CWD dependency, claim-journal failure rollback, daemon continuation after claim failure, and reconcile partial-cleanup reporting.\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs` - add RAII-style project writer-lock acquisition/release around `run start` and `run resume`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs` - remove process-global CWD mutation, downgrade claim-time failures to per-task handling, and report shutdown cleanup failures accurately\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/task_service.rs` - make claim journaling rollback-atomic and introduce explicit failure-class/cleanup behavior for partial claim persistence\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/lease_service.rs` - return accurate reconcile results with explicit cleanup-failure reporting and stricter release accounting\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/mod.rs` - factor any shared lock/reporting traits or types needed by both CLI and daemon callers\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` - support shared project-lock access and richer reconcile failure persistence/reporting\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/daemon.rs` - surface reconcile cleanup failures in CLI output and exit status\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs` - add end-to-end regressions for writer-lock contention, reconcile failure summaries, and daemon continuation after claim failure\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/automation_runtime_test.rs` - add unit/service tests for claim rollback invariants and reconcile partial-failure accounting\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/daemon_lifecycle.feature` - add public daemon cleanup/reporting scenarios\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_resume_retry.feature` - add public run lock-contention/resume safety scenarios\n- `.gitignore` - ignore transient `.ralph/tmp/` and `.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock` artifacts\n- `.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock` - remove tracked transient session lock file\n- `.ralph/tmp/logs/ralph-resume-016.log` - remove tracked runtime log artifact\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: Loop 11 (Daemon Routing, Tasks, Leases, and Worktree Management), Loop 16 (Daemon Issue Watchers and Requirements Handoff), and existing run lifecycle slices through Loop 14\n- Blocks: Project completion request\n\n---"}}
